# Claude Code Project Configuration (DSO Plugin Example)
#
# EXAMPLE: Copy to your project root as CLAUDE.md and customize.
# This template is for projects that have installed the DSO plugin via
# `bash .claude/scripts/dso dso-setup.sh .` (shim form).
#
# All DSO scripts are invoked through the shim: `.claude/scripts/dso <script-name>`
# The shim resolves DSO_ROOT from CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT env var or workflow-config.conf.

**Repo root**: `<your-repo-root>` — all script paths below are relative to this.

## Working Directory & Paths

**ALWAYS run `pwd` first** to confirm your working directory before running commands.

**Worktree sessions**: If in a worktree (`test -f .git`), use `REPO_ROOT=$(git rev-parse --show-toplevel)`. See `.claude/scripts/dso docs WORKTREE-GUIDE.md`.

## Quick Reference

| Action | Command | When Run |
|--------|---------|----------|
| Run epics end-to-end | `/dso:sprint` | Starting a feature epic |
| Feature ideation to epic spec | `/dso:brainstorm` | New feature exploration |
| Epic decomposition into stories | `/dso:preplanning` | After epic creation |
| Story to task breakdown | `/dso:implementation-plan` | Before coding a story |
| Diagnose and fix failures | `/dso:debug-everything` | Test/CI/runtime failures |
| Commit with review gates | `/dso:commit` | Ready to commit |
| Code review via sub-agent | `/dso:review` | Pre-commit review |
| Review plans/designs | `/dso:plan-review` | Before presenting a plan |
| Clean session close | `/dso:end` | End of session |
| Full validation suite | `.claude/scripts/dso validate.sh --ci` | Before merge / after epic |
| Check unqualified skill refs | `.claude/scripts/dso check-skill-refs.sh` | After editing in-scope files |
| Bulk-qualify skill refs | `.claude/scripts/dso qualify-skill-refs.sh` | One-shot migration (run once) |
| Merge worktree to main | `.claude/scripts/dso merge-to-main.sh` | Worktree session complete |
| Check CI status | `.claude/scripts/dso ci-status.sh --wait` | After git push |
| Estimate context load | `.claude/scripts/dso estimate-context-load.sh debug-everything` | Before /dso:debug-everything |
| Run batched tests | `.claude/scripts/dso test-batched.sh --timeout=50 "make test"` | Long-running test suites |
| Validate ticket health | `.claude/scripts/dso validate-issues.sh --quick --terse` | After creating/updating tickets |
| List ready tickets | `.claude/scripts/dso ticket list` | Check what to work on |
| Show ticket details | `.claude/scripts/dso ticket show <id>` | Inspect a specific ticket |

Priority: 0-4 (0=critical, 4=backlog). Never use "high"/"medium"/"low".

## Architecture

**Hook architecture**: DSO hooks run via the plugin root. See your `workflow-config.conf` for `dso.plugin_root` configuration.

**Validation gate**: `.claude/scripts/dso validate.sh` writes state; hooks block sprint/epic if validation hasn't passed.

**Host project script invocation**: All DSO scripts are called via `.claude/scripts/dso <script-name>` (shim). The shim resolves DSO_ROOT from `CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT` env var or `dso.plugin_root` in `workflow-config.conf`.

## Critical Rules

1. **Never close tasks before CI passes** — fix if you broke it; create tracking issue if pre-existing.
2. **Never use `--no-verify`** without human approval.
3. **Never skip issue validation after creating issues or adding deps** — run `.claude/scripts/dso validate-issues.sh --quick --terse`.
4. **Never exceed the usage-aware sub-agent cap** — `orchestration.max_agents` (`dso-config.conf`) sets the upper bound; when absent, `MAX_AGENTS` is unlimited. Throttle tiers override: 90%/95% (5hr/7day) usage → `MAX_AGENTS: 1`; 95%/98% → `MAX_AGENTS: 0` (pause all dispatch). Always check the effective cap before launching a batch.
5. **Never use raw `git commit`** — use `/dso:commit` or the commit workflow. Review gate blocks raw commits.
6. **Never bypass the review gate** — run `/dso:commit` to satisfy it.

## Task Completion Workflow

```bash
# 1. /dso:commit — auto-runs /dso:review if needed, then commits.
# 2. git push (or .claude/scripts/dso merge-to-main.sh in worktree sessions)
# 3. .claude/scripts/dso ci-status.sh --wait — must return "success"
# 4. .claude/scripts/dso ticket transition <id> in_progress closed --reason="Fixed: <summary>"
```

**Session close**: Use `/dso:end`.
